  "text": "Previous work suggested a prosurvival role of ␤-catenin at the pre-TCR stage. [CITATION_1] The authors deleted the portion of the ␤-catenin gene, which encodes the phosphorylation sites in the ␤-catenin protein that determine protein turnover. The accumulation of stable ␤-catenin induced thymocyte differentiation (without proliferation) and survival past the DN3 stage even in the absence of a pre-TCR. Thus, an excess of stable ␤-catenin may compensate for the lack of pre-TCR-dependent TCF-1 induction and allow the aberrant survival of pre-TCR-deficient thymocytes. This highlights the need for cells lacking a pre-TCR, to control TCF/catenin signaling to prevent T-cell development past the DN3 stage. The pre-TCRdependent induction of TCF-1 seems to ensure that only pre-TCR ϩ thymocytes benefit from the prosurvival function of the wnt pathway.",
  "correct_citation": {
